  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LPRR response pilot in Southern Shan State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The local NGOs involved Dear Myanmar agree to develop their own simple plans for piloting the LPRR approach. This is primarily to help them prepare themselves and make sure they know who within their own organisation is overseeing the pilot and to ensure that the staff involved are sufficiently confident in the approach being piloted.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This is the first step in helping your organisation to test and develop new ways of emergency programming that focus on strengthening communities&#x2019; opportunities and capacities to respond themselves to the crises that they are facing. These approaches have emerged from the experiences of local CSOs in many countries including Myanmar, but need to be adapted to fit in particular contexts so that they can then test them in practice as part of your on-going work</narrative>
  </description>
